Processing uploaded files is extremely dangerous because many file formats (SVG, XML, PDF, DOCX) can contain embedded URLs or external entity references that trigger server-side requests. The 2023 GitLab SSRF vulnerability (CVE-2023-5831) allowed attackers to upload malicious files that caused the server to make requests to internal services.

