**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- SVG files can contain XXE payloads that fetch internal resources
- Image metadata (EXIF/XMP) can contain malicious URLs that get fetched
- `file_get_contents()` on user-controlled URLs enables SSRF to internal services
- AWS/GCP/Azure metadata endpoints (169.254.169.254) can expose credentials
- Internal APIs and services become accessible through the server

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
class SecureImageProcessor {
    private $uploadDir = '/var/www/uploads/';
    private $allowedMimeTypes = ['image/jpeg', 'image/png', 'image/gif', 'image/webp'];
    private $maxFileSize = 10485760; // 10MB

    public function processUpload($file) {
        // Validate file before processing
        $this->validateUpload($file);

        // Generate safe filename
        $extension = $this->getSafeExtension($file);
        $filename = $this->uploadDir . bin2hex(random_bytes(16)) . '.' . $extension;

        move_uploaded_file($file['tmp_name'], $filename);

        // Extract metadata safely without following URLs
        $metadata = $this->extractMetadataSafely($filename);

        // Never fetch external URLs from uploaded content
        // If needed, queue for async processing with strict validation

        return [
            'filename' => basename($filename),
            'metadata' => $metadata
        ];
    }

    private function validateUpload($file) {
        if ($file['error'] !== UPLOAD_ERR_OK) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Upload failed');
        }

        if ($file['size'] > $this->maxFileSize) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('File too large');
        }

        // Verify actual MIME type, not just extension
        $finfo = new finfo(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE);
        $mimeType = $finfo->file($file['tmp_name']);

        if (!in_array($mimeType, $this->allowedMimeTypes, true)) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid file type: ' . $mimeType);
        }

        // Block SVG files entirely due to XXE risks
        if (stripos($mimeType, 'svg') !== false) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('SVG files not allowed');
        }

        // Verify image is actually valid
        $imageInfo = @getimagesize($file['tmp_name']);
        if ($imageInfo === false) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid image file');
        }
    }

    private function getSafeExtension($file) {
        $finfo = new finfo(FILEINFO_MIME_TYPE);
        $mimeType = $finfo->file($file['tmp_name']);

        $mimeToExt = [
            'image/jpeg' => 'jpg',
            'image/png' => 'png',
            'image/gif' => 'gif',
            'image/webp' => 'webp'
        ];

        return $mimeToExt[$mimeType] ?? 'bin';
    }

    private function extractMetadataSafely($filename) {
        // Only extract safe metadata fields
        $safeFields = ['Width', 'Height', 'MimeType', 'DateTime'];
        $exif = @exif_read_data($filename);

        if (!$exif) {
            return [];
        }

        $safeMetadata = [];
        foreach ($safeFields as $field) {
            if (isset($exif[$field])) {
                // Sanitize the value
                $safeMetadata[$field] = htmlspecialchars(
                    substr((string)$exif[$field], 0, 255),
                    ENT_QUOTES,
                    'UTF-8'
                );
            }
        }

        return $safeMetadata;
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **File type validation**: Verifies actual MIME type using finfo, not just extension
- **SVG blocking**: Completely blocks SVG files which can contain XXE payloads
- **No external URL fetching**: Never follows URLs found in uploaded content
- **Safe metadata extraction**: Only extracts whitelisted, sanitized metadata fields
- **Random filenames**: Prevents path traversal and predictable file locations

