```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **URL Normalization**: Decode multiple encoding layers to catch `%2525252f` → `/` attacks
```javascript
// Catch triple-encoded payloads
let decoded = urlString;
let iterations = 0;
do {
  prevDecoded = decoded;
  decoded = decodeURIComponent(decoded);
} while (decoded !== prevDecoded && iterations++ < 5);
```

2. **IP Deobfuscation**: Catch decimal, octal, hex, and IPv6-mapped addresses
```javascript
// 2130706433 → 127.0.0.1
// 0177.0.0.1 → 127.0.0.1 (octal)
// 0x7f.0.0.1 → 127.0.0.1 (hex)
// ::ffff:127.0.0.1 → 127.0.0.1 (IPv6 mapped)
```

3. **DNS Pinning**: Lock the resolved IP to prevent rebinding attacks
```javascript
const agent = new https.Agent({
  lookup: (hostname, opts, callback) => {
    callback(null, pinnedIP, 4); // Always use our validated IP
  }
});
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Post-connection validation**: Check socket.remoteAddress after connection to detect time-of-check-time-of-use (TOCTOU) attacks
- **Short DNS cache TTL**: 60 seconds prevents stale records but limits rebinding window
- **Cloud metadata blocking**: Explicit blocks for AWS (169.254.169.254), Azure (168.63.129.16), and GCP metadata endpoints
- **Structured logging**: Every request logged with unique ID for forensic analysis
- **Rate limiting**: Prevent enumeration and DoS via URL fetching
- **Metrics collection**: Track blocked requests and rebinding attempts for security monitoring
- **Zero redirect policy**: Block all redirects to prevent redirect-based SSRF bypass

Image metadata extraction is a common SSRF attack vector. The GitLab CVE-2021-22205 demonstrated how attackers can embed malicious URLs in image metadata (like EXIF data or SVG files) that get processed server-side, causing the server to make requests to internal resources.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import org.apache.commons.imaging.Imaging;
import org.apache.commons.imaging.common.ImageMetadata;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile;
import javax.imageio.ImageIO;
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.io.*;
import java.net.URL;

@RestController
public class ImageUploadController {

    private static final String UPLOAD_DIR = "/uploads/";

    @PostMapping("/api/upload/image")
    public String uploadImage(@RequestParam("file") MultipartFile file) throws Exception {
        // VULNERABLE: No validation of file content
        String filename = file.getOriginalFilename();
        File destFile = new File(UPLOAD_DIR + filename);
        file.transferTo(destFile);

        // VULNERABLE: Processing SVG files can trigger SSRF via external entities
        if (filename.endsWith(".svg")) {
            return processSvgFile(destFile);
        }

        // VULNERABLE: Image metadata extraction can follow URLs
        ImageMetadata metadata = Imaging.getMetadata(destFile);

        // VULNERABLE: Thumbnail generation may fetch external resources
        BufferedImage image = ImageIO.read(destFile);

        return "Image processed: " + metadata.toString();
    }

    private String processSvgFile(File svgFile) throws Exception {
        // VULNERABLE: SVG can contain external entity references
        javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory factory = 
            javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
        javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilder builder = factory.newDocumentBuilder();
        org.w3c.dom.Document doc = builder.parse(svgFile);
        return "SVG processed";
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload** - Malicious SVG file:
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE svg [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/">
]>
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100" height="100">
  <text x="10" y="50">&xxe;</text>
  <image xlink:href="http://internal-server:8080/admin/config" />
</svg>
```

**Attack Payload** - Malicious EXIF data:
```bash
exiftool -ImageDescription='http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/' malicious.jpg
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- SVG files can contain XXE payloads that fetch internal URLs during XML parsing
- Image processing libraries may follow URLs embedded in metadata fields
- Cloud metadata endpoints (169.254.169.254) can leak AWS/GCP credentials
- Attackers can scan internal networks through uploaded files

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import javax.imageio.ImageIO;
import java.awt.image.BufferedImage;
import java.io.*;
import java.security.MessageDigest;
import java.util.*;

@RestController
public class SecureImageUploadController {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureImageUploadController.class);
    private static final String UPLOAD_DIR = "/uploads/";
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_TYPES = Set.of("image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/gif");
    private static final Set<byte[]> MAGIC_BYTES = Set.of(
        new byte[]{(byte)0xFF, (byte)0xD8, (byte)0xFF},  // JPEG
        new byte[]{(byte)0x89, 0x50, 0x4E, 0x47},        // PNG
        new byte[]{0x47, 0x49, 0x46}                      // GIF
    );
    private static final long MAX_FILE_SIZE = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10MB

    @PostMapping("/api/upload/image")
    public String uploadImage(@RequestParam("file") MultipartFile file) {
        try {
            // DEFENSE 1: Validate file size
            if (file.getSize() > MAX_FILE_SIZE) {
                logger.warn("File size exceeded: {}", file.getSize());
                return "Error: File too large";
            }

            // DEFENSE 2: Validate content type (don't trust header alone)
            String contentType = file.getContentType();
            if (contentType == null || !ALLOWED_TYPES.contains(contentType.toLowerCase())) {
                logger.warn("Invalid content type: {}", contentType);
                return "Error: Only JPEG, PNG, and GIF allowed";
            }

            // DEFENSE 3: Validate magic bytes (actual file content)
            byte[] fileBytes = file.getBytes();
            if (!validateMagicBytes(fileBytes)) {
                logger.warn("Magic bytes validation failed for upload");
                return "Error: Invalid image format";
            }

            // DEFENSE 4: Re-encode image to strip metadata and embedded content
            BufferedImage sanitizedImage = sanitizeImage(fileBytes);
            if (sanitizedImage == null) {
                logger.warn("Image sanitization failed");
                return "Error: Could not process image";
            }

            // DEFENSE 5: Generate random filename to prevent path traversal
            String safeFilename = generateSafeFilename(contentType);
            File destFile = new File(UPLOAD_DIR + safeFilename);

            // DEFENSE 6: Write sanitized image (stripped of all metadata)
            String format = contentType.equals("image/png") ? "PNG" : "JPEG";
            ImageIO.write(sanitizedImage, format, destFile);

            logger.info("Image uploaded successfully: {}", safeFilename);
            return "Image uploaded: " + safeFilename;

        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Upload error", e);
            return "Error: Upload failed";
        }
    }

    private boolean validateMagicBytes(byte[] fileBytes) {
        for (byte[] magic : MAGIC_BYTES) {
            if (fileBytes.length >= magic.length) {
                boolean matches = true;
                for (int i = 0; i < magic.length; i++) {
                    if (fileBytes[i] != magic[i]) {
                        matches = false;
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (matches) return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    private BufferedImage sanitizeImage(byte[] imageBytes) throws IOException {
        // Re-encode image to strip all metadata and embedded content
        ByteArrayInputStream bais = new ByteArrayInputStream(imageBytes);
        BufferedImage originalImage = ImageIO.read(bais);
        if (originalImage == null) return null;

        // Create new image with only pixel data (no metadata)
        BufferedImage sanitized = new BufferedImage(
            originalImage.getWidth(),
            originalImage.getHeight(),
            BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_RGB
        );
        sanitized.getGraphics().drawImage(originalImage, 0, 0, null);
        return sanitized;
    }

    private String generateSafeFilename(String contentType) throws Exception {
        String extension = contentType.equals("image/png") ? ".png" : 
                          contentType.equals("image/gif") ? ".gif" : ".jpg";
        String uuid = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
        return uuid + extension;
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Magic byte validation**: Verifies actual file content matches claimed type, preventing disguised malicious files
- **Image re-encoding**: Strips all metadata and embedded URLs by re-rendering only pixel data
- **SVG/XML rejection**: Blocks vector formats that can contain XXE/SSRF payloads
- **Random filename generation**: Prevents path traversal attacks via malicious filenames

Supporting SVG safely requires extremely careful sanitization since SVG is essentially XML that can contain scripts, external references, and embedded objects. Here's a production-ready approach with multiple defense layers.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```java
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile;
import org.w3c.dom.*;
import org.xml.sax.InputSource;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import javax.xml.parsers.*;
import javax.xml.transform.*;
import javax.xml.transform.dom.DOMSource;
import javax.xml.transform.stream.StreamResult;
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

@RestController
public class SecureSvgUploadController {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(SecureSvgUploadController.class);
    private static final long MAX_SVG_SIZE = 5 * 1024 * 1024; // 5MB

    // Allowlist of safe SVG elements
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_ELEMENTS = Set.of(
        "svg", "g", "path", "rect", "circle", "ellipse", "line", 
        "polyline", "polygon", "text", "tspan", "defs", "clipPath",
        "linearGradient", "radialGradient", "stop", "mask", "use",
        "symbol", "title", "desc"
    );

    // Allowlist of safe attributes
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_ATTRIBUTES = Set.of(
        "id", "class", "style", "d", "fill", "stroke", "stroke-width",
        "x", "y", "width", "height", "cx", "cy", "r", "rx", "ry",
        "x1", "y1", "x2", "y2", "points", "transform", "viewBox",
        "xmlns", "version", "preserveAspectRatio", "opacity",
        "font-family", "font-size", "text-anchor", "offset",
        "stop-color", "stop-opacity", "gradientUnits", "clip-path"
    );

    // Dangerous patterns to block
    private static final List<Pattern> DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = List.of(
        Pattern.compile("javascript:", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("data:", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("vbscript:", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("file:", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("http://", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("https://", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("//", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("<!ENTITY", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("<!DOCTYPE", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("SYSTEM", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE),
        Pattern.compile("PUBLIC", Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE)
    );

    @PostMapping("/api/upload/svg")
    public Map<String, Object> uploadSvg(@RequestParam("file") MultipartFile file) {
        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();
        String requestId = UUID.randomUUID().toString();

        try {
            logger.info("SVG upload started, requestId={}", requestId);

            // DEFENSE 1: Size validation
            if (file.getSize() > MAX_SVG_SIZE) {
                logger.warn("SVG too large: {} bytes, requestId={}", file.getSize(), requestId);
                response.put("error", "File too large");
                return response;
            }

            String rawContent = new String(file.getBytes(), "UTF-8");

            // DEFENSE 2: Pre-parse content check for dangerous patterns
            for (Pattern pattern : DANGEROUS_PATTERNS) {
                if (pattern.matcher(rawContent).find()) {
                    logger.warn("Dangerous pattern detected in SVG, requestId={}", requestId);
                    response.put("error", "Invalid SVG content");
                    return response;
                }
            }

            // DEFENSE 3: Parse with secure XML parser (XXE disabled)
            Document doc = parseSecureXml(rawContent);
            if (doc == null) {
                response.put("error", "Invalid SVG format");
                return response;
            }

            // DEFENSE 4: Sanitize DOM tree (element and attribute allowlist)
            sanitizeSvgDom(doc.getDocumentElement());

            // DEFENSE 5: Remove all event handlers and scripts
            removeScriptElements(doc);

            // DEFENSE 6: Serialize sanitized SVG
            String sanitizedSvg = serializeDom(doc);

            // DEFENSE 7: Final validation pass
            for (Pattern pattern : DANGEROUS_PATTERNS) {
                if (pattern.matcher(sanitizedSvg).find()) {
                    logger.error("Dangerous pattern survived sanitization, requestId={}", requestId);
                    response.put("error", "SVG validation failed");
                    return response;
                }
            }

            // Save sanitized SVG
            String filename = UUID.randomUUID().toString() + ".svg";
            File destFile = new File("/uploads/svg/" + filename);
            try (FileWriter writer = new FileWriter(destFile)) {
                writer.write(sanitizedSvg);
            }

            logger.info("SVG uploaded successfully: {}, requestId={}", filename, requestId);
            response.put("success", true);
            response.put("filename", filename);
            return response;

        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("SVG upload error, requestId={}", requestId, e);
            response.put("error", "Upload failed");
            return response;
        }
    }

    private Document parseSecureXml(String xmlContent) throws Exception {
        DocumentBuilderFactory factory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();

        // CRITICAL: Disable all external entity processing
        factory.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);
        factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities", false);
        factory.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities", false);
        factory.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/nonvalidating/load-external-dtd", false);
        factory.setXIncludeAware(false);
        factory.setExpandEntityReferences(false);

        DocumentBuilder builder = factory.newDocumentBuilder();
        return builder.parse(new InputSource(new StringReader(xmlContent)));
    }

    private void sanitizeSvgDom(Element element) {
        // Remove element if not in allowlist
        String tagName = element.getTagName().toLowerCase();
        if (!ALLOWED_ELEMENTS.contains(tagName)) {
            element.getParentNode().removeChild(element);
            return;
        }

        // Remove disallowed attributes
        NamedNodeMap attributes = element.getAttributes();
        List<String> toRemove = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < attributes.getLength(); i++) {
            Node attr = attributes.item(i);
            String attrName = attr.getNodeName().toLowerCase();
            String attrValue = attr.getNodeValue();

            // Block event handlers
            if (attrName.startsWith("on")) {
                toRemove.add(attr.getNodeName());
                continue;
            }

            // Block href/xlink:href with URLs
            if (attrName.contains("href") || attrName.contains("xlink")) {
                if (!attrValue.startsWith("#")) { // Only allow internal references
                    toRemove.add(attr.getNodeName());
                    continue;
                }
            }

            // Check attribute value for dangerous patterns
            for (Pattern pattern : DANGEROUS_PATTERNS) {
                if (pattern.matcher(attrValue).find()) {
                    toRemove.add(attr.getNodeName());
                    break;
                }
            }

            // Only keep explicitly allowed attributes
            if (!ALLOWED_ATTRIBUTES.contains(attrName) && !attrName.startsWith("xmlns")) {
                toRemove.add(attr.getNodeName());
            }
        }

        for (String attr : toRemove) {
            element.removeAttribute(attr);
        }

        // Recursively process children
        NodeList children = element.getChildNodes();
        List<Node> childList = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < children.getLength(); i++) {
            childList.add(children.item(i));
        }

        for (Node child : childList) {
            if (child instanceof Element) {
                sanitizeSvgDom((Element) child);
            }
        }
    }

    private void removeScriptElements(Document doc) {
        // Remove script, foreignObject, and other dangerous elements
        String[] dangerousElements = {"script", "foreignObject", "iframe", 
            "embed", "object", "animate", "set", "handler", "listener"};

        for (String tagName : dangerousElements) {
            NodeList elements = doc.getElementsByTagName(tagName);
            while (elements.getLength() > 0) {
                Node element = elements.item(0);
                element.getParentNode().removeChild(element);
            }
        }
    }

    private String serializeDom(Document doc) throws Exception {
        TransformerFactory tf = TransformerFactory.newInstance();
        tf.setAttribute("http://javax.xml.XMLConstants/property/accessExternalDTD", "");
        tf.setAttribute("http://javax.xml.XMLConstants/property/accessExternalStylesheet", "");

        Transformer transformer = tf.newTransformer();
        transformer.setOutputProperty(OutputKeys.OMIT_XML_DECLARATION, "no");
        transformer.setOutputProperty(OutputKeys.INDENT, "no");

        StringWriter writer = new StringWriter();
        transformer.transform(new DOMSource(doc), new StreamResult(writer));
        return writer.toString();
    }
}
```

